Catherine encouraged me to set up mental speed bumps so that I would be forced to think for a second before engaging with my phone.
What else?”For the rest of the week, I became acutely aware of the bizarre phone habits I’d developed.
For years, I’ve used my phone every time I’ve had a spare moment in an elevator or a boring meeting.
So during my morning walk to the office, I looked up at the buildings around me, spotting architectural details I’d never noticed before.
Catherine had warned me that I might feel existential malaise when I wasn’t distracting myself with my phone.